The Nigeria Centre for Disease Control, NCDC, on Monday hinted that Coronavirus is airborne. Director-General of NCDC, Dr. Chikwe Ihekweazu disclosed this during the Presidential Taskforce on COVID-19 daily briefing in Abuja. Ihekweazu disclosed that more evidence indicates that the virus can be transmitted by air other than through droplets. He explained: “On Case management, priority henceforth will be having enough oxygen nationwide as the number of hospitalized person increases “There is increasing evidence that in addition to droplets transmission of COVID-19, airborne transmission is also possible. “PTF will strictly enforce non-pharmaceutical regulations following the latest finding that COVID-19 can be airborne.”